text: You are doing well. Give yourself a pat on the shoulder first. My first 4 weeks I have anxiety attacks, anger attacks, cabin fever and other things I wanted to forget now 😅. But after that I managed to step out of that vicious cycle. For once, stop seeing negative news, if you like singing, sing on karaoke app, do things you like, let the kids do things they like. Eat ice cream, dance a bit! But I feel exercising everyday helps a lot. During this tough times, everyone must learn to say sorry and forgive and forget. Love and compassion is what we need now. Stay strong! Everything comes to an end and so does this. It’s just how we choose to ride thru the journey that counts. 💪❤️

text: Virtual hugs to you dearest Amelia ❤️ same struggles, different household - for me, I’ve set some ground rules for when they need me, there are pockets of time when they can reach out else WFM will basically be out of the window; fighting wise, I’ve tried my best to rationalise with them and to be honest, there were occasions where I just left them be and get them to sort things out themselves. You’ll be surprised but they do knock it off and settle down. We can’t be all things for them and be there for them all the time. Try to let go, for your own sanity. And most importantly, ring fence your rest time - a time where you just rest as you like or to do things you enjoy ❤️

text: Oh dear, hope you are feeling better after a good night rest🤗I guess with boys is alot tougher. 😓😓Why not just ignore them and go to your own room, have a cup of lavender or chamomile tea to relax. Tell them to behave themselves in a calm voice, (don't even raise your voice), otherwise no lunch or dinner for them. No need for them to argue as the rule has been set. Skipping a meal won't kill. Boys got to learn the tough way. I do that to my nephews & nieces, (all below 10) when they stay with me during their annual December school holidays, cos their parents need a break from them.😅😅 All 4 of them, so imagine the possible ruckus. I just talk to them like my staff & I give them a daily 'briefing' every morning regarding the day's schedule & what I expect them to do and what they can look forward to if they behave well. Anyone who misbehaves will forfeit their treat of the day. Works really well for me😆Don't beat yourself up for disciplining them. Misbehaviour needs to be corrected. Pray for strength & guidance every morning before you start your day🙏 I hope this helps😚🤗
